cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC 

This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks and the integration of logic-based and distributional semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses probabilistic logic inference, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Markov Logic Networks (MLNs) is a machine learning technique, which is covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses knowledge base construction and the integration of different sources, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of probabilistic inference, which is covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
